<subSubSection id="BCFBD083735ABB26867035F5C92B6291" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="48F98B949C3064AF2A94F1B8CB5E66E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C7FF6FF97D0E438E27306CA977D6E371" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
[Slovenia] Carniola, Mojakrana, Aljazev dom, 1100 m, 1931, 
<normalizedToken id="43FA6AED57AC7239CEDFC83103448568" originalValue="Servít">Servit</normalizedToken>
(PRM-858477!, holotype?).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D735CB90CF8E738C7A89C021C297478F" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph id="716B4F355958A368BDEFB0683715F93A" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7AD9022F192ABFAA0DC755652F61508B" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus white, endolithic. Perithecia 0.11-0.36 mm, immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock. Involucrellum absent. Exciple ca. 0.25 mm in diam., wall dark. Periphysoids ca. 25-35 
<normalizedToken id="BB1E5891240BD8D783EF8C08855C3AEF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, sparsely branching, 
<taxonomicName id="AE4937A599D9FE322D2627915F4F8291" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Bagliettoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bagliettoa" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="543DE83AD70E873966E564C049CF70F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Bagliettoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like. Ascospores 0-septate (only few seen), 15-18 
<normalizedToken id="43E947A3BFE3F9A1636BEBF8520E15DE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="45DECEBD171434C6F1F368FE61DCD39A" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph id="75E2AC488C96DF0B9223FB53AF184058" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="98BBD3E1F2F76CA0DF5FBE802928A224" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
According to the protologue (
<bibRefCitation id="53BD9BF2587247FA23834457283C318B" author="Servit, M" journalOrPublisher="Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="67 - 115" refId="B48" refString="Servit, M, 1948. The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II. Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca 9: 67 - 115" title="The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II." volume="9" year="1948">
<normalizedToken id="68CDB5C9765859D0DA68899B4B85C6FE" originalValue="Servít">Servit</normalizedToken>
1948
</bibRefCitation>
), the spore size is 20-28 
<normalizedToken id="AD42D513FB0D76ED5114AEAAE8CEB4F8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-8 mm. The species may be related to 
<taxonomicName id="6C7B8EDA58D31766DE6C5488A710EF57" authorityName="Gueidan &amp; Cl. Roux" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="DC." class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Bagliettoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bagliettoa calciseda" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="calciseda">
<emphasis id="C3645C955D9FAD48EDEE1942965ED556" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Bagliettoa calciseda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) Gueidan &amp; Cl. Roux.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
